Enter your green economy innovation business idea to stand a chance of pitching to a panel of esteemed judges at a shark-tank-style hybrid networking event, hosted in Cape Town in May 2022. Network with potential investors, business incubators, local government decision-makers and green economy experts. Prizes, including a cash prize and in-kind business support, are sponsored by RMB, BioCiti Labs, LaunchLab and SAREBI, with more to be confirmed. "Through our partnership with GreenCape, the City can capitalise on vast opportunities in the Green Economy. Our innovative partnering model has helped to realise more job and growth opportunities in one of the world’s fastest-growing and most important industries. The green economy has massive potential to attract investment that leads to job creation. Initiatives like these give us a platform to empower businesses and communities to innovate and take action to grow the green economy, and thereby creating jobs,” said Alderman James Vos, mayoral committee member for Economic Growth. One of the means of specifically promoting sustainability innovation is through green economy business innovation. The 2022 GreenPitch Challenge speaks to the need for spurring innovation, and providing a testing ground for entrepreneurs to pilot their business venture. Enabling such innovation aligns to the City of Cape Town’s Inclusive Economic Growth Strategy in that it seeks to foster the retention and expansion of businesses in Cape Town.Entry requirementYour green economy innovation business idea has to be positioned within at least one of the Green Economy sectors – refer to the investment opportunities highlighted in GreenCape’s 2021 Market Intelligence Reports. Your business can be based anywhere in South Africa, but you need to have a presence in Cape Town (currently or planned).Who should enter?Innovators and entrepreneurs with economically viable green economy innovation business ideas. The business idea has to be in the pre-venture (ideation, conceptual) or pre-growth (registered and trading/break-even) phase. The judging panel will consider these two categories separately, and there will be a top five selected from both categories to make up the top ten finalists. Why enter?Access to the eco-system of green economy support. Prizes, including a cash prize and in-kind business support, are sponsored by RMB, BioCiti Labs, LaunchLab and SAREBI. More details to follow. How to enterFill out the digital entry form available online here. The digital form allows you to submit a 500-word written motivation. Key datesGreenPitch Challenge entries open: Monday, 14 March 2022Closing date for entries: Thursday, 31 March 2022 @ 12pmFinalists announced: Tuesday, 12 April 2022Coaching for pitch event: 19–29 April 2022Pitch event: Thursday, 5 May 2022The winner will be selected by a judging panel on the day of the event. Their decision is final. Terms & conditions apply.